                <!-- Step-by-Step Setup -->
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-3xl font-semibold font-display mb-4">
                        Step-by-Step Setup
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-sans">
                        Follow these steps to install Tailwind CSS via npm and configure it with PostCSS:
                    </p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside ml-6 space-y-2 mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl font-sans">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Initialize npm:</strong> In your project directory, run:
                            <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-bash">
npm init -y
</code>
                            </pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Install Tailwind CSS:</strong> Run:
                            <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-bash">
npm install tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
</code>
                            </pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Create Configuration Files:</strong> Generate <code>tailwind.config.js</code> and <code>postcss.config.js</code>:
                            <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-bash">
npx tailwindcss init -p
</code>
                            </pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Configure Tailwind:</strong> Set up your template paths and customize your theme in <code>tailwind.config.js</code>.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Include Tailwind in Your CSS:</strong> Create a CSS file (e.g., <code>src/styles.css</code>) and add:
                            <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-css">&commat;tailwind base;
&commat;tailwind components;
&commat;tailwind utilities;
</code>
                            </pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Build Your CSS:</strong> Run the Tailwind CLI to compile your CSS:
                            <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-bash">
npx tailwindcss -i ./src/styles.css -o ./dist/styles.css --watch
</code>
                            </pre>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
